yay, ok, more good news

#1 - got my final paper for my freshmen seminar class. it says that it's due on the 21st, which is amazingly great becasue that's the class that i was going to have the final on the 23rd for. soo....that means, no final on the 23rd! wooohoooo....now, i can go home one day earlier....or wait, more good news?...

#2 - realized that my psych paper is due on the 22nd...on, or BEFORE! so, if i'm a good little girly and get it done early, i can possibly go home the day before that. after my social issues final (3 hours, fun fun) on the 21st. 

YAYAYAYAYAYAYAYAYYAYAYAYAYAY!

and, plus, tonight's movie night, so double woohoo.
and, plus, plus, everything is wonderful in the world of jessica anne roth
and, plus, plus, plus, i had a really nice/cute chat with my dad tonight. that made me really happy.

goooooood day all around.
leave happy comments :-)

ok, so i had a really great break
it was too short and didn't get to see some people i wanted to, but for the most part i was very happy with what i got to do and who i did get to see. ps. i really have the sweetest bf and at times i don't think that i deserve him because i'm a jerk, but i really do appreciate and love him immensely.

it's nice to be back, though...whoa, who said that? *looks over shoulder*
but really, it's weird, i get work done and feel so independent here, which is really great for me.
getting up for 8 o'clock classes aren't that fun, though...but, there's not many of those left, thank god.

anyway, the reason of this entry is to share a song with you guys. jamie listens to really great music, all different kinds, and most of them are really great. anyone ever heard of the spill canvas? well, i hadn't, but now i really like them. this song is her and ergin's song, and i can't help but love it. you really have to hear it to get the full effect, i think...it's worth downloading...it's called "so much"

happy halloween everyone!
nobody gets dressed up here, so that was kind of disappointing
my suitemates and i and a few other people are planning on going trick of treating tonight and possibly to a cemetery...i'm kind of deathfully scared, but hopefully it won't be too bad...jamie wants to visit all the weird nj things, but lets just pray not tonight. i think a visit to a cemetery on halloween is enough scaryness for one day. ;-p

today was pretty good
i had an 8 oclock class, but got up at 7 perfectly fine and wasn't even tired...shocker! and we got back an essay and i got an A-! i feel so proud of myself (and it was about friends, so i guess i have all you guys to thank for that... :-) )
and i have an exam due on thursday for psych, but i did that this afternoon...let's hope i do better than last time *cross fingers*
i still have a paper to write for tomorrow, but not till 3:30, so i'll definitely get that done sometime.

i had a pretty good weekend home
i hugged my kitchen stool - that's how homesick i was *blushes*
it was good to see my family and matt, even if it just was for a little bit
hehe, i miss jenny! it was so good to see her too...i miss melissa too...she wasn't home, though...hopefully next time

i love this cd - trisha yearwood jasper county...GREAT cd (yes, it's country, but it's amazing...and country music is the best, btw)

sorry, i know this is all useless information for you all, but i felt like updating and needed to do something besides my paper. hehe.

again, i hope everyone had a great halloween. i can't wait till thanksgiving...really, i can't. it needs to come...like, now.
aw, and then it's christmas! jesus, i won't know what to do with myself. i'm going to be so happy!

love you xoxoxo

ps. i miss abbegail cohen sooooOOoooooo much :-(
pps. i miss highschool...WHAT? who said that?? all the memories were so great...for the most part...i love you matt

woohoo!! summer's been absolutely great so far and hopefully will only get better. i love my family and my friends so much and they've been a huge part of my wonderful summer.

graduation was a blast. it's hard to believe that those 4 undescribable years are over. as corny as it sounds, it seems like just yesterday i was scared to death to enter this huge school and meet new people. wow, it's really weird but amazing at the same time to think back at everything that's happened and changed in just 4 years.  i've made some beautiful friends and met the best boyfriend possible. and as for the friends i've kept, i'll always keep. they're my rock. *kisskiss*

i'm scared to leave for college. i know that what happens happens, but a huge part of me wants things to stay the same. gaurenteed it's going to be hard on friendships and relationships because we won't see each other everyday, but i'm really confident that i will remain close to those whom i can't live without. i'm trying to get excited for ramapo, but i don't know. i can't shake the feeling of being the outsider and not making any new friends. hopefully everything'll be okay, though. i just have to believe that or i'm in trouble.

thanks to everyone.
:D

great poem...

ee cummings is a cool guy...

somewhere i have never travelled

somewhere i have never travelled,gladly beyond
any experience,your eyes have their silence:
in your most frail gesture are things which enclose me,
or which i cannot touch because they are too near

your slightest look easily will unclose me
though i have closed myself as fingers,
you open always petal by petal myself as Spring opens
(touching skilfully,mysteriously) her first rose

or if your wish be to close me,i and
my life will shut very beautifully, suddenly,
as when the heart of this flower imagines
the snow carefully everywhere descending;

nothing which we are to perceive in this world equals
the power of your intense fragility: whose texture
compels me with the color of its countries,
rendering death and forever with each breathing

(i do not know what it is about you that closes
and opens; only something in me understands
the voice of your eyes is deeper than all roses)
nobody,not even the rain, has such small hands


this one's really sad...but, sweet nonetheless...

it may not always be so; and i say 

it may not always be so;and i say
that if your lips,which i have loved,should touch
another's,and your dear strong fingers clutch
his heart,as mine in time not far away;
if on another's face your sweet hair lay
in such a silence as i know,or such
great writhing words as,uttering overmuch,
stand helplessly before the spirit at bay;
   
if this should be,i say if this should be-
you of my heart,send me a little word;
that i may go unto him,and take his hands,
saying,Accept all happiness from me.
Then shall i turn my face,and hear one bird
sing terribly afar in the lost lands.
